Practice Questions
Q1. Show all columns plus a running total of Amount ordered by SaleID.

   SELECT *, 
        SUM (Amount) OVER (ORDER BY SaleID) AS RunningTotal 
   FROM Sales;

Q2. Show all columns plus a running total of Amount ordered by Amount ASC.

   SELECT *, 
        SUM(Amount) OVER (ORDER BY Amount ASC) AS RunTot 
   FROM Sales;

Q3. Show all columns plus a running total of Amount ordered by Amount DESC.

   SELECT *, 
        SUM(Amount) OVER (ORDER BY Amount DESC) AS RunningTotal
   FROM Sales;

Q4. Show Month, Amount and running total ordered by SaleID.

   SELECT Month, Amount, 
        SUM(Amount) OVER (ORDER BY SaleID) AS RunningTotal 
   FROM Sales;

Q5. Show SaleID, Amount and running total ordered by SaleID.

   SELECT SaleID, Amount, 
           SUM(Amount) OVER (ORDER BY SaleID) AS RunningTotal 
   FROM Sales;
